  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'What is the right melatonin dose for adults?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Sleep researchers increasingly recommend lower melatonin doses than what is commonly sold. A 2013 meta-analysis in PLOS ONE found that doses of 0.5 to 5mg were effective for reducing sleep onset latency. The MIT researchers who pioneered melatonin research found that 0.3mg was sufficient to raise blood melatonin to natural nighttime levels. Most sleep specialists recommend starting at 0.5 to 1mg and increasing to a maximum of 3 to 5mg only if lower doses are ineffective. Higher doses (10mg+) do not improve sleep proportionally and are more likely to cause side effects including vivid dreams, morning grogginess, and headaches.' } },
