  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'What is the difference between regular and extended-release melatonin?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Regular (immediate-release) melatonin raises blood levels within 20 to 40 minutes and is cleared from the body within 4 to 5 hours. This is best for people who have difficulty falling asleep (sleep onset insomnia). Extended-release melatonin releases the hormone gradually over 6 to 8 hours, maintaining elevated levels throughout the night. This is better for people who fall asleep normally but wake up too early or have fragmented sleep (sleep maintenance insomnia). Some gummies now use dual-release technology combining both immediate and sustained release for comprehensive sleep architecture support.' } },
