    <h2 id="melatonin-dosing">The Melatonin Dosing Problem: Why More Is Not Better</h2>

    <p>The melatonin supplement market has a dosing problem. Products ranging from 1mg to 20mg are sold side by side, creating confusion about what adults actually need. The science is clear: your body naturally produces approximately 0.1 to 0.3mg of melatonin per night. Supplemental doses of 0.5 to 3mg are sufficient to raise blood melatonin to levels that effectively signal the circadian clock for sleep. Doses above 5mg provide diminishing returns — they do not improve sleep quality proportionally but do increase the risk of morning grogginess, vivid nightmares, and daytime sleepiness.</p>

