    </div>

    <p>MIT researchers who first studied melatonin supplementation found that 0.3mg was the optimal physiological dose — enough to raise blood melatonin to natural nighttime levels without overwhelming the receptor system. While most commercial products significantly exceed this amount, the clinical consensus from the American Academy of Sleep Medicine favors a "start low, go slow" approach: begin at 0.5 to 1mg and increase to a maximum of 3 to 5mg only if lower doses prove insufficient after 1 to 2 weeks.</p>

